#: Game.Levels.Rewriting.L07_Calc
msgid "Congratulations, this is the end of your first exercise file! You've seen what typing\n"
"a Lean proof looks like and have learned about the following tactics:\n"
"* §0\n"
"* §1\n"
"* §2\n"
"* §3"
msgstr "恭喜，这是你第一个练习文件的结束！你已经看到了输入 Lean 证明是什么样子的，\n"
"并学习了以下策略：\n"
"* §0\n"
"* §1\n"
"* §2\n"
"* §3"

#: Game.Levels.Rewriting.L05_RwLemma
msgid "Rewriting with a lemma"
msgstr "使用引理重写"

#. §0: `add_pos`
#: Game.Levels.Logic.L03_ProvingImplications
msgid "Now use §0 with your new assumptions."
msgstr "现在使用 §0 和你的新假设。"

#: Game
msgid "You should use this game as a template for your own game and add your own levels."
msgstr "你应该使用此游戏作为你自己游戏的模板，并添加你自己的关卡。"

#. §0: `0 < a`
#: Game.Levels.Logic.L01_Implications
msgid "The above proof is a direct proof: we already know §0 and we feed this fact into the\n"
"implication."
msgstr "上面的证明是直接证明：我们已经知道 §0，我们将这个事实输入到蕴含中。"

#. §0: `ring`
#: Game.Levels.Rewriting
msgid "# Computing\n"
"\n"
"## The ring tactic\n"
"\n"
"One of the earliest kind of proofs one encounters while learning mathematics is proving by\n"
"a calculation. It may not sound like a proof, but this is actually using lemmas expressing\n"
"properties of operations on numbers. Of course we usually don't want to invoke those explicitly\n"
"so mathlib has a tactic §0 taking care of proving equalities that follow by applying\n"
"the properties of all commutative rings."
msgstr "# 计算\n"
"\n"
"## ring 策略\n"
"\n"
"学习数学时最早遇到的证明之一是通过计算进行证明。这听起来可能不像证明，但实际上这是在使用表达数运算性质的引理。当然，我们通常不想显式调用这些引理，所以 mathlib 有一个策略 §0，它负责通过应用所有交换环的性质来证明等式。"

#: Game.Levels.Analysis.L01_SequenceLimit
msgid "# Sequence Limits\n"
"\n"
"A sequence `u` is a function from `ℕ` to `ℝ`, hence Lean says `u : ℕ → ℝ`.\n"
"The definition we'll be using is:\n"
"\n"
"`def seq_limit (u : ℕ → ℝ) (l : ℝ) := ∀ ε > 0, ∃ N, ∀ n ≥ N, |u n - l| ≤ ε`\n"
"\n"
"Note the use of `∀ ε > 0, _` which is an abbreviation of `∀ ε, ε > 0 → _`."
msgstr "# 序列极限\n"
"\n"
"序列 `u` 是一个从 `ℕ` 到 `ℝ` 的函数，因此 Lean 称之为 `u : ℕ → ℝ`。\n"
"我们将使用的定义是：\n"
"\n"
"`def seq_limit (u : ℕ → ℝ) (l : ℝ) := ∀ ε > 0, ∃ N, ∀ n ≥ N, |u n - l| ≤ ε`\n"
"\n"
"注意 `∀ ε > 0, _` 的用法，这是 `∀ ε, ε > 0 → _` 的缩写。"

#. §0: `«{h}»`
#. §1: `«{h'}»`
#. §2: `rw [«{h}», «{h'}»]`
#: Game.Levels.Rewriting.L04_RwMultiple
msgid "Try rewriting both §0 and §1. You can do it in one command §2 or two."
msgstr "尝试重写 §0 和 §1。你可以在一个命令 §2 中完成，也可以分两次完成。"

#: Game.Levels.Analysis.L04_Uniqueness
msgid "Limits are unique in Hausdorff spaces (like ℝ)."
msgstr "极限在豪斯多夫空间（如 ℝ）中是唯一的。"

#. §0: `simp`
#: Game.Levels.Analysis.L01_SequenceLimit
msgid "Simplify §0."
msgstr "简化 §0。"

#: Game.Levels.SetTheory.L01_InfSup
msgid "Infimum and Supremum"
msgstr "下确界和上确界"

#: Game.Levels.Logic.L07_Conjunction
msgid "# Conjunction\n"
"\n"
"To prove `P ∧ Q`, use the `constructor` tactic. This will split the goal into two subgoals: prove `P`, then prove `Q`.\n"
"To use an assumption `h : P ∧ Q`, you can decompose it using `rcases h with ⟨hP, hQ⟩` or `have ⟨hP, hQ⟩ := h`."
msgstr "# 合取\n"
"\n"
"要证明 `P ∧ Q`，请使用 `constructor` 策略。这将把目标分成两个子目标：先证明 `P`，然后证明 `Q`。\n"
"要使用假设 `h : P ∧ Q`，你可以使用 `rcases h with ⟨hP, hQ⟩` 或 `have ⟨hP, hQ⟩ := h` 对其进行分解。"

#: Game.Levels.Logic.L04_Equivalences
msgid "We can prove this equivalence by proving both directions."
msgstr "我们可以通过证明两个方向来证明这个等价关系。"

#: Game.Levels.Logic.L05_Forall
msgid "# Universal Quantifiers\n"
"\n"
"To prove a goal of the form `∀ x, P x`, you can use `intro x`.\n"
"To use an assumption `h : ∀ x, P x`, you can specialize it to a specific value using `specialize h my_value`\n"
"or simply apply it to the value: `have hp := h my_value`."
msgstr "# 全称量词\n"
"\n"
"要证明形式为 `∀ x, P x` 的目标，你可以使用 `intro x`。\n"
"要使用假设 `h : ∀ x, P x`，你可以使用 `specialize h my_value` 将其专门化为特定值\n"
"或者简单地将其应用于该值：`have hp := h my_value`。"

#. §0: `h'`
#: Game.Levels.Logic.L05_Forall
msgid "Now we know `f 0 ≤ g 0`. Use §0 to finish."
msgstr "现在我们知道 `f 0 ≤ g 0`。使用 §0 完成。"

#. §0: `ε`
#. §1: `ε_pos`
#: Game.Levels.Analysis.L01_SequenceLimit
msgid "Start by introducing §0 and §1."
msgstr "首先引入 §0 和 §1。"

#: Game.Levels.Algebra.L01_RingHom
msgid "`simp` is very effective at simplifying expressions involving ring homomorphisms."
msgstr "`simp` 在简化涉及环同态的表达式方面非常有效。"

#: Game.Levels.SetTheory.L01_InfSup
msgid "# Infimum and Supremum\n"
"\n"
"An element `x₀` is an infimum of a set `s` in `X` if every element of `X` is a lower bound of `s` if and only if it is below `x₀`."
msgstr "# 下确界和上确界\n"
"\n"
"如果 `X` 的每个元素是 `s` 的下界当且仅当它小于等于 `x₀`，则元素 `x₀` 是 `X` 中集合 `s` 的下确界。"

#: Game.Levels.Probability.L01_Independence
msgid "Commutativity of intersection and multiplication."
msgstr "交集和乘法的交换律。"

#. §0: `N`
#: Game.Levels.Analysis.L01_SequenceLimit
msgid "We need to provide a natural number §0. Any number will do since the sequence is constant."
msgstr "我们需要提供一个自然数 §0。任何数字都可以，因为序列是常数序列。"

#. §0: `u n`
#. §1: `l`
#. §2: `h`
#: Game.Levels.Analysis.L01_SequenceLimit
msgid "Rewrite §0 to §1 using §2."
msgstr "使用 §2 将 §0 重写为 §1。"

#. §0: `exp (a + b - c)`
#. §1: `exp_sub`
#: Game.Levels.Rewriting.L05_RwLemma
msgid "Start by expanding §0 using §1."
msgstr "首先使用 §1 展开 §0。"

