msgid "Simplify §0 using §1."
msgstr "使用 §1 简化 §0。"

#: Game.Levels.Probability
msgid "Probability"
msgstr "概率"

#: Game.Levels.Analysis.L03_SqueezeTheorem
msgid "Squeeze Theorem"
msgstr "夹逼定理"

#. §0: `ring`
#: Game.Levels.Rewriting.L01_Associativity
msgid "One of the earliest kind of proofs one encounters while learning mathematics is proving by\n"
"a calculation. It may not sound like a proof, but this is actually using lemmas expressing\n"
"properties of operations on numbers. Of course we usually don't want to invoke those explicitly\n"
"so mathlib has a tactic §0 taking care of proving equalities that follow by applying\n"
"the properties of all commutative rings."
msgstr "学习数学时最早遇到的证明之一是通过计算进行证明。这听起来可能不像证明，但实际上这是在使用表达数运算性质的引理。当然，我们通常不想显式调用这些引理，所以 mathlib 有一个策略 §0，它负责通过应用所有交换环的性质来证明等式。"

#. §0: `0 < a^2`
#. §1: `sq_pos_of_pos`
#. §2: `ha`
#: Game.Levels.Logic.L02_Forward
msgid "Now prove §0 using §1 and §2."
msgstr "现在使用 §1 和 §2 证明 §0。"

#: Game.Levels.Logic.L06_Exists
msgid "Existential Quantifiers"
msgstr "存在量词"

#. §0: `x`
#. §1: `x + 1 = 2`
#: Game.Levels.Logic.L06_Exists
msgid "Provide a real number §0 such that §1."
msgstr "提供一个实数 §0 使得 §1。"

#: Game.Levels.Probability.L01_Independence
msgid "# Independent Sets\n"
"\n"
"Two sets `A` and `B` are independent if `ℙ (A ∩ B) = ℙ A * ℙ B`."
msgstr "# 独立事件\n"
"\n"
"如果 `ℙ (A ∩ B) = ℙ A * ℙ B`，则两个集合 `A` 和 `B` 是独立的。"

#: Game.Levels.Analysis.L03_SqueezeTheorem
msgid "# Squeeze Theorem\n"
"\n"
"If `u n ≤ v n ≤ w n` and `u` and `w` both tend to `l`, then `v` also tends to `l`."
msgstr "# 夹逼定理\n"
"\n"
"如果 `u n ≤ v n ≤ w n` 且 `u` 和 `w` 都趋向于 `l`，那么 `v` 也趋向于 `l`。"

#: Game.Levels.Rewriting.L06_RwReverse
msgid "Correct! You used reverse rewriting."
msgstr "正确！你使用了反向重写。"

#: Game.Levels.Algebra.L01_RingHom
msgid "# Ring Homomorphisms\n"
"\n"
"Given a ring `R` and a ring `S`, a ring homomorphism from `R` to `S` is written `f : R →+* S`.\n"
"It preserves addition, multiplication, zero, and one."
msgstr "# 环同态\n"
"\n"
"给定一个环 `R` 和一个环 `S`，从 `R` 到 `S` 的环同态写作 `f : R →+* S`。\n"
"它保持加法、乘法、零和一。"

#: Game.Levels.Logic.L07_Conjunction
msgid "Conjunction `∧` represents \"and\"."
msgstr "合取 `∧` 代表“与”。"

#: Game.Levels.Probability.L01_Independence
msgid "Independence is a symmetric relation."
msgstr "独立性是对称关系。"

#: Game.Levels.Analysis.L04_Uniqueness
msgid "# Uniqueness of Limits\n"
"\n"
"A sequence cannot converge to two different limits."
msgstr "# 极限的唯一性\n"
"\n"
"一个序列不能收敛于两个不同的极限。"

#: Game.Levels.Logic.L04_Equivalences
msgid "Equivalences are powerful because they allow you to rewrite propositions."
msgstr "等价关系非常强大，因为它们允许你重写命题。"

#: Game.Levels.Probability
msgid "# Probability\n"
"\n"
"In this world, we explore probability measures, independent sets, and Bayes' theorem."
msgstr "# 概率\n"
"\n"
"在这个世界中，我们探索概率测度、独立事件和贝叶斯定理。"

#: Game.Levels.SetTheory
msgid "# Set Theory\n"
"\n"
"In this world, we explore Galois connections (adjunctions) between complete lattices."
msgstr "# 集合论\n"
"\n"
"在这个世界中，我们探索完备格之间的 Galois 连接（伴随）。"

#: Game.Levels.SetTheory
msgid "Set Theory"
msgstr "集合论"

#: Game.Levels.Rewriting.L01_Associativity
msgid "The ring tactic"
msgstr "ring 策略"

#: Game.Levels.Logic.L04_Equivalences
msgid "Second direction: assume `a = c - b`, prove `a + b = c`."
msgstr "第二方向：假设 `a = c - b`，证明 `a + b = c`。"

#: Game.Levels.Logic.L04_Equivalences
msgid "# Equivalences\n"
"\n"
"The equivalence `A ↔ B` is just the conjunction of `A → B` and `B → A`.\n"
"You can prove it using `constructor` if the goal is `A ↔ B`.\n"
"If you have an assumption `h : A ↔ B`, you can use `rw [h]` to replace `A` with `B`."
msgstr "# 等价\n"
"\n"
"等价 `A ↔ B` 只是 `A → B` 和 `B → A` 的合取。\n"
"如果目标是 `A ↔ B`，你可以使用 `constructor` 来证明它。\n"
"如果你有一个假设 `h : A ↔ B`，你可以使用 `rw [h]` 将 `A` 替换为 `B`。"

#: Game.Levels.Probability.L01_Independence
msgid "Independent Sets"
msgstr "独立事件"

